{"slug":"navbar","framework":"core","source":"<div class=\"page\">\n  <div class=\"navbar\">\n    <div class=\"navbar-bg\"></div>\n    <div class=\"navbar-inner sliding\">\n      <div class=\"left\">\n        <a class=\"link back\">\n          <i class=\"icon icon-back\"></i>\n\n        </a>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"title\">Navbar<span class=\"subtitle\">Subtitle</span></div>\n      <div class=\"right\">\n        <a class=\"link\">Right</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"page-content\">\n    <div class=\"block\">\n      <p>Navbar is a fixed (with Fixed and Through layout types) area at the top of a screen that contains Page title\n        and navigation elements.</p>\n      <p>Navbar has 3 main parts: Left, Title and Right. Each part may contain any HTML content.</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"list list-strong inset-md list-outline-ios links-list\">\n      <ul>\n        <li><a href=\"/navbar-hide-scroll/\">Hide Navbar On Scroll</a></li>\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n"}